The paper deals with image reconstruction using deep learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sparse data is also a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
